## 3. EMBEDDING THE DIALECTIC INTO TEMPO SYSTEMS

### 3.1 Dialectic ↔ Luck Engine
Luck engine equation: $\text{Luck} = S \times T \times V \times I(t)$.

Dialectic strengthens: S (State) through paradox naming; T (Timing) through parallax; V (Vector) through transformation; I(t) (Intuition) through invariant clarity. **Everything multiplies.**

### 3.2 Dialectic ↔ Wave Rider
The dialectic is the inner map, Wave Rider is the outer technique. Together: Inner clarity, outer motion, smooth execution, minimized resistance, maximized alignment.

### 3.3 Dialectic ↔ Web Convergence
The dialectic decides which signals matter, which vectors align, which threads converge, and when to anchor the center. Web convergence then magnifies your moves.

### 3.4 Dialectic ↔ Propagation Theory
The dialectic extracts the invariant. Propagation spreads the invariant. This prevents dilution or corruption of ideas.

